=EN>Peter332</A> at: 7/1/02 7:13:48 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udakkainxxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DakkainXXX</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/ring20.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 203<br> <font color=#333333>(7/1/02 8:20:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1425.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Spell effects</span><hr size=1> To my understanding:<br><br>The DoT would stay active, if mob died to it corpse would poof like it was killed by an NPC.<br><br>Zone would wipe aggro and you would not get reaggroed when you zoned back in even if DoT was still going.<br><br><br>Might be wrong, wouldnt be the first time. <p><font color=MAROON>Dakon Edgecrusher<BR>60 Assassin <BR>Zebuxoruk<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5493 >Inspect Me </a>  </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umanaspineblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Manas Pineblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>It's Mr. Noodleneck </span><br>  Posts: 1270<br> <font color=#333333>(7/1/02 8:21:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1425.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Spell effects</span><hr size=1> DOT's only agro when the spell hits the mob.  From there you gain residual agro from the damage being done.  <br><br>If you leave the zone before the DOT is finished, you will be off the hate list.  The mob will still be dot'ed, but when mobs have no one to hate, they regenerate at an increased rate, usually negating any dot they might have on them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ulewick.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lewick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#333333>(7/1/02 12:52:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1425.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Spell effects</span><hr size=1> You get a new &quot;Player ID&quot; when you zone.  Each time you zone, the server assigns you an ID.  That ID is carried with you for your duration in the zone.  When you cast a spell on a mob, the mob places your ID in their hate list.  If it's a DoT, it also puts the spell on their buff list along with whose ID it is.<br><br>So when you zone, the spell is still on their buff list, but it has no attached ID to match it with, since you zoned and Player IDs are unique upon zoning.  The Player ID is removed from the mob's hate list when you zone.  When you zone back, since you're given a unique Player ID each time you zone, the agro will be clear.<br><br>There were two old bugs with how DoTs worked.  The oldest one was caused by the DoT on a mob causing the death of the mob without an associated Player ID attached to the DoT.  This caused the mob's body to poof when it died.  This bug was around back before they increased the size of the agro list.  Back then the agro list was either 6 or 10 long, maximum.  So it was very easy for, say, a Necro to fall off the agro list on a raid.  This happened a lot in Hate and Fear.<br><br>The first bug was somewhat fixed with the expanded agro list.  However, I believe if a Necro dies while they have a DoT on a mob and the mob dies from the necro dot, it will still poof.  I don't think they've ever fixed that.<br><br> <p><center><table border="1" bordercolor="#000000" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0"><tr><td align="center" valign="center"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif" size="2"><strong> Lewick Goodheart</strong></br></font>Warder<BR>Final Uprising<BR>Zebuxoruk Server</td></tr></table></center> </p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=1425.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showNextMessage?topicID=1425.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1425.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.emailToFriend?topicID=1425.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.threadControl?topicID=1425.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1425.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1425.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub41.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForu